recipe.notes:
This recipe was pretty sweet as there's an odd left hand positioning one to the right that makes one line particularly hard to read.  Fortunately one of my other interests is programming and it uses one of my favorite little-used operators, tr///.  tr/// is a relic of times past, its format strange and long -- the programming equivalent of a komodo dragon.

Perl example:
my $phrase = 'esyrt.  Sff juivr ftsinrf gtom pinrspplr.  Uhill until';

$phrase =~ tr/sdfgSDFGwertWERTxcvbXCVB/asdfASDFqwerQWERzxcvZXCV/;

print $phrase;
